The method get(IBundleProvider results) makes a database request, calling it twice that's two database requests. We can optimize this to only one DB request.
This is how;
List<IBaseResource> locations = get(search(theParams));
assertThat(locations, notNullValue());
assertThat(locations.size(), equalTo(1));
assertThat(((Location) locations.iterator().next()).getName(), equalTo(LOCATION_NAME));
Actually I made the same mistake 🤦🏾‍♂️ in observation resource, sorry my bad.

